com.ibm.mobile.services.data

Class IBMDataObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.mobile.services.data.IBMDataObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    IBMDevice, IBMUser

    public class IBMDataObject
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is the base object type. Other classes can specialize this class but this interface will handle all of the low level object management actions.

      • reapplySaves

        public boolean reapplySaves(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> unsavedFields,
                   java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> dirtyFields)
                     throws IBMDataException
        The reapplySaves method is a provisional API. APIs that are marked provisional are evolving and might change or be removed in future releases. This method is used by a registered IBMDataObjectDelegate to reapply a set of client changes to a conflict.
        Parameters:
        unsavedFields - A dictionary of pending saves to the object's fields.
        dirtyFields - A dictionary of changes to an object's fields that were not specifically saved.
        Returns:
        Indicates whether the saves and dirty values could be reapplied.
        Throws:
        IBMDataException

      • fetchIfNecessary

        public  fetchIfNecessary()
        This method asynchronously loads data from the server for this instance of theIBMDataObject with the ability to chain additional tasks. If Data is already available it is a no-op.
        Returns:
        A task containing the results of the operation
